<Layout title="Join" currentPage="join">
  <h2>Joining the group</h2>

  <p>
    We are generally interested in recruiting undergraduates, graduate students, and
    postdoctoral scholars with interests applying mathematical and computational tools to
    conceptual questions in evolution and ecology. Folks whose interests overlap with
    previous <a href="/research/">research</a> and <a href="/publications/">publications</a>
    from the lab are certainly encouraged to contact us.
  </p>

  <p>
    Additionally, the lab aims to be broadly interdisciplinary across complex biological
    systems from the molecular to metapopulation scales, and we welcome inquiries from
    folks with diverse backgrounds including (but not limited to) mathematics, physics,
    computer science, and economics.
  </p>

  <ul class="bulleted">
    <li>
      <strong>Graduate students:</strong> The lab is currently accepting graduate students through the
      <a href="http://bio.as.uky.edu/grad-program" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Biology Graduate Program</a>
      at UK.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Postdoctoral scholars:</strong> Inquiries from prospective postdocs are actively encouraged.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    When contacting the lab about potentially joining, please send an email with a short
    summary of your research interests and your CV attached in PDF format.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Email:</strong>
    <a href="mailto:jvancleve@uky.edu">jvancleve –at– uky –dot– edu</a>
  </p>
</Layout>
